Package: accerciser
Version: 3.22.0-7
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Debian Accessibility Team <pkg-a11y-devel@lists.alioth.debian.org>
Installed-Size: 6078
Depends: dconf-gsettings-backend | gsettings-backend, python3:any, ipython3 (>= 0.12), gir1.2-atk-1.0, gir1.2-gdkpixbuf-2.0, gir1.2-glib-2.0, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, gir1.2-pango-1.0, gir1.2-rsvg-2.0, gir1.2-wnck-3.0, python3-cairo, python3-gi-cairo, python3-xlib, python3-pyatspi (>= 2.5.2)
Section: gnome
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://wiki.gnome.org/Apps/Accerciser
Description: interactive Python accessibility explorer for the GNOME desktop
 It uses AT-SPI to inspect and control widgets, allowing you to check if
 an application is providing correct information to assistive technologies
 and automated test frameworks. Accerciser has a simple plugin framework which
 you can use to create custom views of accessibility information.
